Informed consent to participate in research

In this study, we are interested in how people make decisions. If you agree to be in this study, you will play a decision-making game, as well as answer some brief demographic questions. The estimated time to complete this study is approximately 7 minutes. The research is being conducted with the goal of publication in academic journals and presentation at academic conferences.



Risks

Your participation in this study does not involve any physical risk or emotional risk to you beyond the risks of daily life.



Compensation

You will receive the amount specified in the description of the study for your participation. In addition, you may earn a bonus based on your decision in the game, as detailed in the instructions of the study.

The bonus will be paid after some delay - once we have collected the responses of all the participants in the study. 



Confidentiality

The data you provide will be collected through a secure online system called Qualtrics. The collected data will be fully anonymized and confidentiality will be maintained. We may report the data in scientific publications and the data may ultimately be stored in online repositories so that other researchers can utilize this information in future research. However, any such data will be completely anonymized and you will not in any way be identifiable from the data stored online or reported in publications.



Contacts

If there is anything about the study or taking part in it that is unclear or that you do not understand, please contact the researcher of this study, through a message in the messaging system.



Subject rights

Participation in this study is voluntary, and you are free to leave the study at any time. If you withdraw at any time, you will receive no monetary compensation.

Do you agree to participate? Please click below if you agree to participate in the research.

 

Please note: there are a few questions that will test your attention throughout the survey. Please pay close attention, and answer carefully. Participants who fail an attention check will not be paid.
education level: What is the highest level of school you have completed or the highest degree you have received?
attention check 1_1: People vary in the amount they pay attention to these kinds of experiments. Some take them seriously and read each question, whereas other go very quickly and barely read the questions at all. If you have read this question carefully, please write down the word yes in the blank box below labeled other. There is no need for you to respond to the scale below.
comprehension 1: How many players will play the game with you? (NOT including yourself)
comprehension 2: How many envelopes can you choose from?
comprehension 4: Imagine that there is a square in the envelope chosen by the other player and that you found a circle in your envelope. In such a scenario, what would be the amount of your bonus, and the amount of the other player's bonus?
comprehension 5: Imagine that there is a kitein the envelope chosen by the other player and that you found a kite in your envelope. In such a scenario, what would be the amount of your bonus, and the amount of the other player's bonus?
comprehension 3: Imagine you have been assigned the color ORANGE. Can you choose a BLUE envelope?
